Mahindra Holidays, Reliance, Yes Bank: India Stocks Preview

-- B y   A n d r e w   M a c A s k i l l   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-02-23T02:53:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/reliance-industries-mahindra-holidays-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
142.15, or 0.8 percent, to 18,296.16. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on
the National Stock Exchange declined 0.9 percent to 5,469.20.
The BSE 200 Index decreased 0.9 percent to 2,243.93. SGX S&P CNX
Nifty Index futures for February delivery fell 0.7 percent to
5,435.5 at 10:49 a.m. in  Singapore .  Reliance Industries (RIL IN): Niko Resources Ltd. can
increase its stake in oil and gas blocks operated by Reliance
Industries in India by 30 percent of its current holdings after
the Indian company formed a partnership with BP Plc, Reliance
said in an e-mailed statement.  Separately, Reliance Industries and BP Plc may expand their
relationship and jointly participate in downstream opportunities
in India, including auto fuel retailing, the Mint newspaper
reported, citing two unidentified people familiar with the
development. The stock gained 3 percent to 984.85 rupees.    Mahindra Holidays & Resorts India Ltd . (MHRL IN): The owner
of the Club Mahindra Holidays brand appointed Rajiv Sawhney as
chief executive officer. The shares rose 1.7 percent to 356.4
rupees.    Yes Bank Ltd . (YES IN): The lender with branches in more
than 100 locations around the country was rated “overweight”
in new coverage at JPMorgan Chase & Co., which said the bank’s
“differentiated” approach will pay off as it leverages a
“superior” wholesale franchise into a wider retail base. The
brokerage initiated its share-price estimate at 350 rupees,
according to a report by analysts led by Seshadri K Sen. The
shares dropped 2.5 percent to 275.05 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
